definition.value: A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 3-phosphate(3-) arising from deprotonation of all three free phosphate OH groups of 1,2-dioctanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-D-myo-inositol-3'-phosphate); major species at pH 7.3.
A polyunsaturated fatty acid whose structure contains double bonds at any four positions of a 36-carbon straight chain.
A polyunsaturated fatty acid whose structure contains double bonds at any five positions of a 36-carbon straight chain.
A polyunsaturated fatty acid whose structure contains double bonds at any six positions of a 36-carbon straight chain.
A polyunsaturated fatty acid whose structure contains double bonds at any four positions of a 38-carbon straight chain.
A polyunsaturated fatty acid whose structure contains double bonds at any five positions of a 38-carbon straight chain.
An N-acylphosphatidylethanolamine in which the N-acyl group is specified as palmitoyl while the phosphatidyl acyl groups are both specified as oleoyl.

The 2-aminoethyl glycoside of an amino decasaccharide made of two alpha-L-Rhap-(1->2)-alpha-L-Rhap-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Glcp-(1->4)]-alpha-L-Rhap-(1->3)-beta-D-GlcpNAc repeating units of the Shigella flexneri serotype 2a specific polysaccharide linked (1->2).

The 2-aminoethyl glycoside of an amino decasaccharide made of two alpha-L-Rhap-(1->2)-alpha-L-Rhap-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Glcp-(1->4)]-alpha-L-Rhap-(1->3)-beta-D-GlcpNAc repeating units of the Shigella flexneri serotype 2a specific polysaccharide linked (1->2) and with the rhamnose residue four residues from the reducing end acetylated on O-3.
An ammonium ion resulting from the protonation of both of the tertiary amino groups of pipamperone.

The 2-aminoethyl glycoside of an amino decasaccharide made of two alpha-L-Rhap-(1->2)-alpha-L-Rhap-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Glcp-(1->4)]-alpha-L-Rhap-(1->3)-beta-D-GlcpNAc repeating units of the Shigella flexneri serotype 2a specific polysaccharide linked (1->2) and with the rhamnose residue four residues from the reducing end the N-acetylglucosamine residue five residues from the reducing end acetylated on O-3 and O-6 respectively.

The 2-aminoethyl glycoside of an amino decasaccharide made of two alpha-L-Rhap-(1->2)-alpha-L-Rhap-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Glcp-(1->4)]-alpha-L-Rhap-(1->3)-beta-D-GlcpNAc repeating units of the Shigella flexneri serotype 2a specific polysaccharide linked (1->2) and with the N-acetylglucosamine residue five residues from the reducing end acetylated on O-6.
Any prokaryotic metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in  single-celled microorganisms, archaea.

An L-alpha-amino acid zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of L-2-amino-3-oxobutanoic acid. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).
An (omega-1)-hydroxy fatty acid that is octanoic acid in which the 7-pro-R hydrogen has been replaced by a hydroxy group.
